\f0\fs26 \cf0 34. 
\b The Stairwell : trapdoor, beds, ghost
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 What appears to long forgotten beds and tables moulder in this large chamber. Set before the north wall is a heavy and ironshod double trapdoor, no doubt leading into deeper regions of the dungeon. A sturdy bar seals the way. 
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The beds and tables are crumbling and of no value. The appear to have been about six beds, that would have been for roughly human sized occupants. 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 If the bar is moved, the characters can lift open the double doors revealing a spiral stairway leads down into the darkness. The skeleton of a human or half elf lies someway down and a ghost haunts the stairs who reveals some information about the Toolizth Coven before attempting to push characters down the stairs. The stairs leads to subsection of the 2nd level. Trap.}